This paper deals with the problem of iterated localization in wireless sensor networks, which is a topic related to networked systems and information theory. Therefore, cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) and cs.IT (Information Theory) are the most likely sub-categories. The paper also involves the use of algorithms and data structures for efficient localization, which falls under cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). Additionally, the paper discusses the probabilistic analysis of the localization process, which is related to cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) and cs.SY (Systems and Control).
